# Worker and RabbitMQ

- Redis is not the queue — jobs go through RabbitMQ
- Manual ack only after DB reflects terminal job state (or safe retry path)
- Never ack if DLQ publish failed — Nack(requeue) instead
- Max 5 jobs in flight; transient failures go to `{queue}.retry` with per-message TTL (no in-process sleep holding the slot)
- Rate-limit waits use `CountAsAttempt=false` and must not burn `WORKER_MAX_RETRIES`
- Permanent failures → DLQ with reason; update batch job row accordingly
- Idempotent processing: duplicate delivery must not double-count batch success/failure
- Refresh-all uses batch kick + fan-out; kick redelivery recovers mid-loop publish failure
- Publisher confirms on enqueue paths
- SIGTERM: stop consuming, finish or requeue in-flight, no lost messages
